<div class="content-header">Linux Scripts</div>

<div class="content">
    Linux scripts have the following general features:
    <ul>
        <li>Scripts that have file input also allow piped input (<code>musicXml*</code> scripts except <code>musicXmlProcess</code>, and
            <code>ly2Pdf</code>)</li>
        <li>Scripts with file output can send their output to stdout which can also be piped to another script (<code>*2MusicXml</code> and
            <code>*2Ly</code> scripts)</li>
        <li><code>-h</code> and <code>--help</code> options</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content">
    The scripts are part of the installation, and are also available separately in a zip file <a href="/resources/scripts/linux_scripts.zip">here</a>.
</div>
